<h2>You can search INSPIRE via our <a href="http://inspirebeta.net/help/easy-search">easy search</a> or via the main search box.  The 
search box allows for greater control over the search.  Tips for using it are presented below.<h2>
<h5>Search with SPIRES familiar syntax</h5>
 <table class="tips">
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find a van proeyen and aff ecole normale superieure" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action" value="Search" />
       </form>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs"><p>We have tried to reproduce traditional SPIRES syntax, however, there are subtle differences - many are 
      documented below.  If you find other differences that are bothersome, let us know at <a 
      href="mailto:feedback@inspirebeta.net">feedback@inspirebeta.net</a></p>
     </td>
   </tr>
 </table>
<h5> Search like Google</h5>
 <table class="tips">
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="thomas crewther quark 2002" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action" value="Search" />
       </form>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs">
      <p>Can use any field (author, title, journal, date, page number, affiliation, etc.)</p>
      <p>Similar to traditional SPIRES search:
      <br />
      <br />
      find a thomas and a crewther and t quark and date 2002
      <br />
      </p>  
     </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find a l everett or t light higgs and j phys.rev.lett. and primarch hep-ex" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action" value="Search" />
       </form>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs">
      <p>Search logic:  Logical operators (<b>and, or, not</b>) work left to right.</p>
     </td>
   </tr>
 </table>
<h5>Logical Operators and Truncation</h5>
 <table class="tips">
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
        <p>Logical operators:
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find a l everett or t light higgs and j phys.rev.lett. and primarch hep-ph" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action" value="Search" />
       </form>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs">
      <p>Search logic: Logical operators (<b>and, or, not</b>) work left to right.</p>
     </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
      <p>Truncation:</p>
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find a rober* and t dyso*" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action" value="Search" />
       </form>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs">
      <p>The <a href="http://inspirebeta.net/help/easy-search/">easy search</a> is the easiest way to specify journals but you can 
      also use the search box.</p>
     </td>
   </tr>
 </table>
