<h5>Searching by Field-Code</h5>
 <table class="tips">
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
      <p>Field-codes expand the familiar archive categories to non-eprints.</p>
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find fc t and t higgs mass" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action23" value="Search" />
       </form>
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find fc o and t feynman" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action33" value="Search" />
       </form>
       <form action="/search" method="get">
         <input name="p" type="text" value="find fc g and t eccentric orbits" size="56" />
         <input class="formbutton" type="submit" name="action43" value="Search" />
       </form>
     <td class="tips-rhs"> 
      <p>A - astrophysics - astro-ph</p>
      <p>B - beams - physics-acc-phy</p>
      <p>C - computing</p>
      <p>E - experiment - hep-ex</p>
      <p>G - gravity - gr-qc</p>
      <p>I - instruments - phys.ins-det</p>
      <p>L - lattice - hep-lat</p>
      <p>M - math - math-ph/mh</p>
      <p>N - nuclear theory - nucl-th</p>
      <p>O - other - physics</p>
      <p>P - phenomenology - hep-ph</p>
      <p>Q - quantum - quant-ph</p>
      <p>T - theory - hep-th</p>
      <p>X - (e)xperiment - nucl-ex</p>
     </td> 
   </tr>
 </table>
<h5>More about author searching:</h5>
 <table class="tips">
   <tr>
     <td class="tips-lhs">
      <p>We have a new author identification system.  When you find a paper and click on an author's name,
         you will be taken to the author's publication profile page.</p>
      <p>These pages are created by a program that identifies an author's identity based on name, co-authors and affiliation.
         For most authors it does quite well.  For others, eg. John Smith, it does less well.  Authors are able to help though, by 
         verifying the publication list:&nbsp;&nbsp;claiming their own papers and removing other people's papers.</p>
     </td>
     <td class="tips-rhs">
